==Swedish==

===Etymology===
Compound of [[lördag]] + [[-s-]] + [[godis]]
===Noun===
{{sv-noun-unc-irreg-n|2=lördagsgodiset|3=lördagsgodis}}
'''lördagsgodis''' {{n}} (''uncountable'')

# [[candy]] as a [[Saturday]] treat; 
#:'''1995''':Marianne Hedenbro [http://spraakbanken.gu.se/cgi-bin/konk/konk2art.cgi?plats=3593458&korpus=p95&kontext=1000&grad=2 ''Våra otvivelaktigt goda seder''] - Min pappa var framsynt. Han införde '''lördagsgodis''' redan på 50- talet.
#::"My father was progressive. He introduced candy only as a Saturday treat already in the 50:s."
#:'''2000''':Anna Lena Wik-Thorsell [http://spraakbanken.gu.se/cgi-bin/konk/konk2art.cgi?plats=6954738&korpus=svd00&kontext=0&grad=2 ''Social skillnad visar sig i tänderna''] - Sämre tandborstning, mindre ordning med '''lördagsgodis''' och småätande mellan målen ser hon som orsaker till att de sämre ställda barnen har sämre tänder:...
#::"Less rigorous toothbrushing habits, less discipline with candy as a Saturday treat, and snacking between meals are reasons she advances as causes for the comparatively poor state of teeth among disadvantaged children:..."

====Usage notes====
Used in conjunction with the common custom in Sweden to only allow children to eat candy on Saturdays.